<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="30" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="20.[227,348,302,328]" box="[227,348,302,328]" pageId="20" pageNumber="30">
<heading bold="true" box="[227,348,302,328]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="20" pageNumber="30" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[227,348,302,328]" pageId="20" pageNumber="30">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[226,1438,349,586]" pageId="20" pageNumber="30">
Species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bockwinkel, Becker &amp; Ebbighausen" authorityYear="2009" box="[361,514,349,375]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Taouzitidae" genus="Darkaoceras" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ammonoidea" pageId="20" pageNumber="30" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[361,514,349,375]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="30">Darkaoceras</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
reaching about 
<quantity box="[706,790,349,375]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="20" pageNumber="30" unit="mm" value="60.0">60 mm</quantity>
conch diameter with extremely discoidal, subinvolute conch between 30 and 
<quantity box="[513,599,384,411]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="20" pageNumber="30" unit="mm" value="50.0">50 mm</quantity>
dm (ww/dm = 0.25–0.30; uw/dm = 0.15–0.25). Whorl cross section strongly compressed (ww/wh = 0.45–0.60); venter acute with pronounced keel. Growth lines fine, bundled around the umbilicus, strongly biconvex with moderately high dorsolateral projection and very high and narrow ventrolateral projection; ventrolateral shoulder with weak spiral groove. Suture line with high median saddle, V-shaped prongs of the E lobe, V-shaped L lobe, and shallow and rounded U2 lobe.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
