<subSubSection pageId="22" pageNumber="32" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="22.[227,341,805,831]" box="[227,341,805,831]" pageId="22" pageNumber="32">
<heading bold="true" box="[227,341,805,831]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="22" pageNumber="32" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[227,341,805,831]" pageId="22" pageNumber="32">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="22.[227,1437,851,947]" pageId="22" pageNumber="32">
The specimens from Dillenburg are quite large; smaller specimens from 3 up to 
<quantity box="[1167,1249,851,878]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.8" pageId="22" pageNumber="32" unit="mm" value="38.0">38 mm</quantity>
conch diameter were described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Bockwinkel J. &amp; Korn D. &amp; Ebbighausen V. &amp; Graf S." box="[457,774,886,913]" pageId="22" pageNumber="32" pagination="257 - 274" refId="ref17495" refString="Bockwinkel J., Korn D., Ebbighausen V. &amp; Graf S. 2013 b. Late Givetian ammonoids from Hagen- Herbeck, Donnerkuhle quarry (Devonian, Rhenish Mountains). Neues Jahrbuch fur Geologie und Palaontologie, Abhandlungen 270: 257 - 274. https: // doi. org / 10.1127 / 0077 - 7749 / 2013 / 0369" type="journal article" year="2013">
Bockwinkel 
<emphasis box="[609,671,886,912]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="32">et al.</emphasis>
(2013b)
</bibRefCitation>
from Hagen-Herbeck, northern margin of the Rhenish Mountains.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="22.[227,1436,987,1083]" pageId="22" pageNumber="32">
A similar species to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Matern" baseAuthorityYear="1931" box="[476,623,987,1013]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Taouzitidae" genus="Darkaoceras" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ammonoidea" pageId="22" pageNumber="32" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="galeatum">
<emphasis box="[476,623,987,1013]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="32">D. galeatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Petter" baseAuthorityYear="1959" box="[662,839,987,1013]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Taouzitidae" genus="Darkaoceras" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ammonoidea" pageId="22" pageNumber="32" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="meridionale">
<emphasis box="[662,839,987,1013]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="32">D. meridionale</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but this species differs in having slightly thicker inner whorls. 
<taxonomicName authority="Bockwinkel, Becker &amp; Ebbighausen, 2013" authorityName="Bockwinkel, Becker &amp; Ebbighausen" authorityYear="2013" box="[397,1029,1022,1048]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Taouzitidae" genus="Darkaoceras" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ammonoidea" pageId="22" pageNumber="32" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="velox">
<emphasis box="[397,499,1022,1048]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="32">D. velox</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Bockwinkel J. &amp; Becker R. T. &amp; Ebbighausen V." box="[511,1029,1022,1048]" pageId="22" pageNumber="32" pagination="5 - 65" refId="ref17443" refString="Bockwinkel J., Becker R. T. &amp; Ebbighausen V. 2013 a. Late Givetian ammonoids from Hassi Nebech (Tafilalt Basin, Anti-Atlas, southern Morocco). Fossil Record 16: 5 - 65. https: // doi. org / 10.1002 / mmng. 201300001" type="journal article" year="2013">Bockwinkel, Becker &amp; Ebbighausen, 2013</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
also differs by the broader inner whorls.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
